post_text:
A statement on behalf of Hy-Vee CEO Randy Edeker:

"As we have come to expect, there is never a dull moment at the Indianapolis 500 - and this year was no exception. The Greatest Spectacle in Racing lived up to that title whether viewed by the most diehard racing fan or the more casual, novice fan. The remaining moments of the race already had us on the edge of our seats...and then we saw the drastic ending for the No. 45 Hy-Vee race car. We were truly relieved to see driver Spencer Pigot walk away from today's event. We are extremely proud of his hard work and dedication to make it to this point in his career. On behalf of our 85,000 employees, we congratulate Spencer Pigot and the Rahal Letterman Lanigan Racing team on an amazing race."
